00:00:06,209 --> 00:00:08,418
(The World of the Married)

2
00:00:36,634 --> 00:00:39,667
(The World of the Married)

3
00:00:40,834 --> 00:00:44,268
(Three weeks ago)

4
00:00:44,634 --> 00:00:45,335
Here.

5
00:00:47,959 --> 00:00:51,710
Are you okay about going
back to your old school?

6
00:00:51,868 --> 00:00:53,901
Instead of moving to a new place,

7
00:00:54,934 --> 00:00:56,601
I'd rather face my problem head-on.

8
00:00:56,918 --> 00:00:59,001
Looks like you've found some courage.

9
00:00:59,868 --> 00:01:01,302
I'm glad.

10
00:01:27,667 --> 00:01:29,468
- Dad.
- Hey.

11
00:01:29,567 --> 00:01:30,368
Hey.

12
00:01:30,467 --> 00:01:31,701
Wow, what a delicious smell.

13
00:01:32,667 --> 00:01:34,168
Oh wow.

14
00:01:34,434 --> 00:01:36,567
It's my favorite, grilled fish.

15
00:01:37,667 --> 00:01:39,067
I'm hungry.

16
00:01:39,584 --> 00:01:40,918
Wash your hands first.

17
00:01:41,542 --> 00:01:43,126
I'll get your rice.

18
00:01:43,634 --> 00:01:44,934
Why can't you do anything right?

19
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:47,200
You get scolded by Mom all the time.

20
00:01:48,067 --> 00:01:48,868
Hey.

21
00:01:49,292 --> 00:01:52,501
That's because your mom's
madly in love with me.

22
00:01:52,601 --> 00:01:54,235
-Yeah right.
-Yes.

23
00:01:54,601 --> 00:01:55,835
He's right about that.

24
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,400
See?

25
00:02:01,667 --> 00:02:02,700
Look at his face.

26
00:02:03,267 --> 00:02:04,534
Let's eat. I'm hungry.

27
00:02:09,467 --> 00:02:11,068
How was school?

28
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,667
Same old, same old.

29
00:02:12,751 --> 00:02:14,168
How was your day, sweetie?

30
00:02:16,534 --> 00:02:18,868
I'm going on a business trip
to China next Tuesday.

31
00:02:19,334 --> 00:02:20,302
Really?

32
00:02:20,701 --> 00:02:22,235
Will we hear some good news soon?

33
00:02:22,334 --> 00:02:24,001
I have...

34
00:02:24,534 --> 00:02:25,601
...a good feeling about this.

35
00:02:26,250 --> 00:02:29,084
Your dad is oozing confidence.

36
00:02:29,667 --> 00:02:31,268
What will you get for me in China?

37
00:02:31,367 --> 00:02:35,068
What do you want?
What should I get for you?

38
00:02:35,167 --> 00:02:36,834
You're all I need, Dad.

39
00:02:37,067 --> 00:02:40,701
Wow, Joonyoung.

40
00:02:41,125 --> 00:02:42,626
All I need is your mom.

41
00:02:55,367 --> 00:02:56,567
I'm done.

42
00:02:57,067 --> 00:02:58,768
Okay. Go get some rest.

